        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 9 at 12:58PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 1258 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Matoaka, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Matoaka...
Kegley...
Wenonah...
and Coaldale.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
